Turkey's European Affairs Minister AliBozer will arrive here on Saturday to set a date for hiscountry's long-planned application to join the EuropeanCommunity (EC), expected by early May, diplomats said.    The Turkish embassy here said an application was expected"very soon" but gave no date. But sources close to the embassysaid the application for full EC membership would probably bemade in April, or at the latest, by the first week of May.    Bozer, is due to meet Turkish Prime Minister Turgut Ozal inLondon today to decide on the date of the application, theyadded. REUTER&#3;